COAST region is working to establish large scale farming of palm and sunflower in Kibiti District, in order to promote the growth of agriculture sector and boost income. The Regional Commissioner (RC), Mr Aboubakar Kunenge said in Kibiti District this week that   modern agricultural methods will be used in the farms in order to attain the intended objectives, The RC revealed that while presenting 10 tractors  to  paddy growers  and one power tiller all worth 700m/- . "We have already held talks with the Minister for Agriculture Mr  Hussein Bashe about the plan and our vision is to start with demonstration farms where the farmers will come and learn how to do palm and sunflower modern farming", he said. Mr Kunenge added that, the region is doing well in other commercial crops which are sisal, sesame, cashewnuts, sugarcane, rice, coconuts among others. "Last year, we harvested a total of 11,314 tonnes of sesame worth 28bn/- while this year we have harvested 18, 446 tonnes of the crop worth 58bn/-" he said. As for cashewnuts, he went on to say that, the region had harvested 7,000 tonnes in 2020, a total of 11,000 tonnes in 2021 and13,000 tonnes   last year and  earned a sum of 27.8 bn/-, he revealed. "We expect to harvest a total of 13,000 tonnes to 20,000 tonnes  of cashewnuts  this year", he noted